    "body": "Actually is the opposite @AskAlexSharov. See the diff bellow according to [geth-docs](https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/fundamentals/command-line-options) and compared to erigon client.\r\n\r\nFrom Geth docs:\r\n> --rpc.txfeecap value   (default: 1) Sets a cap on transaction fee (in ether) that can be sent via the RPC APIs (0 =no cap)\r\n\r\n> --txpool.pricelimit value (default: 1) Minimum gas price limit to enforce for acceptance into the pool\r\n\r\n\r\nFrom Erigon client help:\r\n> --txpool.pricelimit value Minimum gas price (fee cap) limit to enforce for acceptance into the pool (default: 1)\r\n\r\nIs that possible to be prioritized this implementation in Erigon? I appreciate your help!",
